One of my residents where I work has permanently put me off from buying a Tesla.
Enlighten us.
Guy's brakes were going bad and I told him so, "Yeah, Dadrobit, I know, I'm letting em all go bad before I take it in. They charge $2,000 for a brake job so I'm getting the most out of em."
I beg your pardon?
Two thousand for brakes?
"Sir, you realize you're getting fleeced right?" "Yeah, Dadrobit, I know. But if I get it serviced anywhere else than the dealership, it voids the car's warranty on everything."
Oh come off it.
Now I don't want to buy a Tesla...

They also "Fixed" his license plate when three of the screws fell out by reattaching it with silicone caulking. No fucking joke. They didn't even replace the screws, just caulked the back of the plate and stuck it on.
That's it, I'm going back to my childhood dream of a Land Rover Defender.
His license plate is once again being held on by a single screw as the caulking almost immediately failed.
That is absolutely ridiculous.
The dealership is 120% fucking over its clients. They're banking on all of them being rich and naieve. Part of the $2,000 brake jobs problems was that, "the brakes were full of dust."
I'm guessing that that's just an excuse for more money?
You don't fucking say?!?! Dust? In Arizona?????
Yes, they are the stereotypical mechanic that throws random shit at the customers for more money.
Honestly pretty angry for the kid, has no idea about cars really.
